article.description: — Kyle Rose scored 26 points to lead Fordham and Elijah Gray hit the game-winning jump shot with two seconds remaining as the Rams knocked off Saint Louis 67-65 on Saturday.
article.headline: Rose's 26, Gray's game-winner lead Fordham past Saint Louis, 67-65
article.linkText: Rose's 26, Gray's game-winner lead Fordham past Saint Louis, 67-65
article.story: ST. LOUIS -- — Kyle Rose scored 26 points to lead Fordham and Elijah Gray hit the game-winning jump shot with two seconds remaining as the Rams knocked off Saint Louis 67-65 on Saturday. Rose had three steals for the Rams (10-12, 4-5 Atlantic 10 Conference). Gray scored 12 points while shooting 4 for 10 (1 for 3 from 3-point range) and 3 of 4 from the free throw line. Romad Dean shot 4 for 6, including 2 for 4 from beyond the arc to finish with 10 points. The Billikens (8-14, 1-8) were led by Bradley Ezewiro, who posted 15 points and six rebounds. Terrence Hargrove Jr. added 13 points and six rebounds for Saint Louis. In addition, Sincere Parker had 13 points. The Billikens extended their losing streak to six in a row. Rose scored nine second-half points for Fordham. Fordham's next game is Tuesday against VCU at home. Saint Louis visits La Salle on Wednesday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
